title: The Townhall Weekend Journal for OCT-18-2013 FRI
description:
The Townhall Weekend Journal for OCT-18-2013 FRI




Friday, October 18, 2013


Shutdown's Over.. Obama Issues DeNiro Kicks to GOP Gut


Weekend Journal



Hugh Hewitt and Karl Rove take a look at the end of the shutdown.

 Hewitt and Tevi Troy discuss what the implications after the conclusion of the shutdown.

 Bill Bennett and James Capretta on what the end of the shutdown means for the Republicans.

 Bennett and Ann Coulter on GOP's need to win elections.

 Dennis Prager on new laws mandating that boys be allowed in girls bathrooms/locker rooms, etc.

 and the implications. 

 Michael Medved and Stephen Meyer on climate hysteria.
 
 George Will vs. Charles Krauthammer on changing the name of the Washington Redskins.


Length: 00:39:50
